[{"location":"index.html#DocsXRefTests","page":"DocsXRefTests","title":"DocsXRefTests","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html","page":"DocsXRefTests","title":"DocsXRefTests","text":"On the page (unlike in the g docstring) can link directly to AbstractSelector because the CurrentModule is Main.","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#API","page":"DocsXRefTests","title":"API","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"index.html","page":"DocsXRefTests","title":"DocsXRefTests","text":"DocsReferencingMain.f\nDocsReferencingMain.g","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#Main.DocsReferencingMain.f","page":"DocsXRefTests","title":"Main.DocsReferencingMain.f","text":"This is the function f.\n\nIt references Documenter.Selectors.AbstractSelector, which resolves only because of a fallback to Main.\n\nSee also g.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"index.html#Main.DocsReferencingMain.g","page":"DocsXRefTests","title":"Main.DocsReferencingMain.g","text":"This is the function g\n\nIf references Main.AbstractSelector, which should resolve, unlike the non-fully-qualified AbstractSelector (even though AbstractSelector is in Main)\n\nSee also f.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"index.html","page":"DocsXRefTests","title":"DocsXRefTests","text":"Documenter.Selectors.AbstractSelector\nDocumenter.hide","category":"page"},{"location":"index.html#Documenter.Selectors.AbstractSelector","page":"DocsXRefTests","title":"Documenter.Selectors.AbstractSelector","text":"Root selector type. Each user-defined selector must subtype from this, i.e.\n\nabstract type MySelector <: Selectors.AbstractSelector end\n\nabstract type First  <: MySelector end\nabstract type Second <: MySelector end\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"type"},{"location":"index.html#Documenter.hide","page":"DocsXRefTests","title":"Documenter.hide","text":"hide(page)\n\n\nAllows a page to be hidden in the navigation menu. It will only show up if it happens to be the current page. The hidden page will still be present in the linear page list that can be accessed via the previous and next page links. The title of the hidden page can be overridden using the => operator as usual.\n\nUsage\n\nmakedocs(\n    ...,\n    pages = [\n        ...,\n        hide(\"page1.md\"),\n        hide(\"Title\" => \"page2.md\")\n    ]\n)\n\n\n\n\n\nhide(root, children)\n\n\nAllows a subsection of pages to be hidden from the navigation menu. root will be linked to in the navigation menu, with the title determined as usual. children should be a list of pages (note that it can not be hierarchical).\n\nUsage\n\nmakedocs(\n    ...,\n    pages = [\n        ...,\n        hide(\"Hidden section\" => \"hidden_index.md\", [\n            \"hidden1.md\",\n            \"Hidden 2\" => \"hidden2.md\"\n        ]),\n        hide(\"hidden_index.md\", [...])\n    ]\n)\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"page.html","page":"Second page","title":"Second page","text":"CurrentModule = Documenter.Selectors","category":"page"},{"location":"page.html#Second-page","page":"Second page","title":"Second page","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"page.html","page":"Second page","title":"Second page","text":"This page is in the context of Documenters.Selectors. Thus, we can directly link to AbstractSelector, but we cannot link to DocsReferencingMain.f. But if we use the fully qualified name, it works: Main.DocsReferencingMain.f.","category":"page"},{"location":"page.html","page":"Second page","title":"Second page","text":"We can also link to Documenter.hide because of the fallback to Main.","category":"page"}]
